# Inner Peak Colorado — Page Layout Standards

All pages in `apps/inner-peak-colorado` must follow the same section padding and content width as the homepage and established condition/program pages. This ensures visual cohesion across every page.

## Section wrapper

Every non-hero section must include `w-full` so the background fills the full viewport:

```tsx
<section className="w-full py-24 px-8 md:px-16 bg-[#FAF8F5]">
```

Acceptable vertical padding variants: `py-24` (standard), `py-20` (compact).  
Do **not** use `py-16` or less for primary page sections.

## Content container

Every section's inner content must be wrapped with:

```tsx
<div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
```

**Never use `max-w-6xl`, `max-w-5xl`, or `max-w-4xl` as the primary content container** on a full page section — these create narrow islands that look inconsistent next to `max-w-7xl` sections.  
`max-w-3xl` and `max-w-2xl` are acceptable only for intentionally centered narrow elements (CTA blocks, pull quotes, editorial intros that are deliberately compact).

## Hero section

Full-page heroes must follow the full-bleed gradient pattern established in `what-we-treat` and `levels-of-care` pages:

```tsx
<section className="relative w-full min-h-[620px] flex items-end overflow-hidden">
  <div className="absolute inset-0">
    <Image src={...} alt={...} fill className="object-cover" priority />
    <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#2C3B2E]/90 via-[#2C3B2E]/65 to-[#2C3B2E]/20" />
    <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-[#2C3B2E]/75 via-transparent to-transparent" />
  </div>
  <div className="relative z-10 w-full px-8 md:px-16 pb-20 pt-40">
    <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      {/* Breadcrumb, h1, description, CTAs */}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

Do **not** use custom split-panel grid layouts (e.g., `grid-cols-[55%_45%]`) for heroes — these create width inconsistencies on wide monitors because the layout isn't capped by `max-w-7xl`.

## Background color palette

Use these backgrounds for section alternation:
- `bg-[#FAF8F5]` — primary cream (default)
- `bg-[#F0ECE1]` — warm cream (alternating)
- `bg-[#2C3B2E]` — dark forest green (emphasis sections, hero)

